Council officers in Scotland are turning up the heat on night-time dog walkers who let their pets poop in public spaces – by tracking culprits using thermal imaging equipment.

The advanced technology – which is usually used to catch criminals and dangerous drivers - is being deployed by Fife Council because the problem of dog mess in Fife has become a major problem.

The thermal cameras will be able to detect the body heat of dogs and their owners - and recently produced poo - from hundreds of yards away.

