The council officers who will be tasked with handing out fines will also be given stab vests to protect themselves from any violent or aggressive dog owners.

A street cleaning survey in the region showed that 88 per cent of respondents rated fouling as a problem in their area, higher than any other street cleaning issue.

The council’s environmental enforcement wardens can hand out fixed penalty fines for dog fouling, litter dropping, abandoned vehicles and fly tipping.

